article.description: Anthony Beane scored 22 points and Leo Vincent added another 17 off the bench as Southern Illinois pulled away from Murray State in the second half to post an 88-73 nonconference win Friday night
article.headline: Beane scores 22, Southern Illinois tops Murray State, 88-73
article.linkText: Beane scores 22, Southern Illinois tops Murray State, 88-73
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. -- Anthony Beane scored 22 points and Leo Vincent added another 17 off the bench as Southern Illinois pulled away from Murray State in the second half to post an 88-73 nonconference win Friday night. Beane hit 7 of 18 shots, including 3 of 8 from long range, and the Salukis shot 54 percent from the field, knocking down 28 of 52 shots from the field, including 7 of 19 (37 percent) from deep. Beane now has 1,548 career points and moved up two spots to eighth all-time on SIU's scoring list. Mike Rodriguez and Sean O'Brien each added 13 points for Southern Illinois, which held a 39-28 rebounding advantage on the Racers. Bryce Jones scored 20 points to lead Murray State, with Wayne Langston adding 15 and Jeffery Moss 12. The victory gives the Salulkis a 17-16 record against Murray State.
